// ============================================================
//  ENCAPSULATION — Interview Cheat Sheet
// ============================================================
//
//  Q: What is Encapsulation?
//  A: Bundling data (fields) and the methods that operate on
//     that data into a single unit (class), and RESTRICTING
//     direct access to the internals.
//
//  Q: WHY do we need it? (This is what interviewers really ask)
//  A: Three reasons:
//
//     1. PROTECT INVARIANTS
//        → Your object should never be in an invalid state.
//        → e.g., BankAccount balance should never go negative.
//        → If balance is public, any code can set it to -5000.
//        → With encapsulation, withdraw() enforces the rule.
//
//     2. HIDE IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS
//        → Tomorrow you might store balance in paisa instead
//          of rupees internally. If balance is private, you
//          just change getBalance() to return balance/100.
//          No other code needs to change.
//        → If balance was public, 500 files might break.
//
//     3. CONTROLLED ACCESS
//        → You decide: read-only? write-only? read-write?
//        → getBalance() exists but NO setBalance() → read-only
//        → deposit()/withdraw() are business methods, not
//          dumb setters.
//
//  Q: Is encapsulation just getters and setters?
//  A: NO! This is a common misconception.
//     Making a field private and adding both getter AND setter
//     is basically the same as making it public — no real
//     protection. True encapsulation means:
//     → Expose BEHAVIOR (deposit, withdraw) not data (setBalance)
//     → Give only the access that's actually needed
//     → A setter that blindly sets a value is NOT encapsulation
//
//  Q: Real-world analogy?
//  A: ATM Machine.
//     → You can't open the machine and grab cash (private fields)
//     → You use the screen/buttons (public methods)
//     → The machine enforces rules: PIN check, daily limit,
//        sufficient balance (validation in methods)
//
// ============================================================
